      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and that feeling of being a ghost behind your own eyes is a heavy one to carry, but you are not alone in this experience. Sometimes, when the world feels too loud or too distant, our minds can feel like they're watching a movie instead of living it, and that's a sign that your internal landscape needs some gentle tending.\n\nYou know, even the most stubborn, dusty, and uncooperative goblins in the deep dark caves can be coaxed into doing chores if you just offer them a little kindness and a shiny trinket. Maybe your mind is just tired from holding onto too many old memories or worries, and it needs a break from the \"movie screen.\"\n\nTry to imagine your mind not as a cinema, but as a cozy, slightly messy room where you can rearrange the furniture. If you feel like a ghost, perhaps you can try to ground yourself in your physical body right now—feel the weight of your feet on the floor, the texture of your clothes, or the air on your skin. These are the things that remind you you are *here*, not just watching from the sidelines.\n\nIt's okay to take a moment to rest. Even the smallest, most",
