      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a incredibly heavy and isolating feeling, like standing in an empty theater while the lights are still on, waiting for a performance that no one is actually watching. It sounds like you are feeling a profound sense of disconnection from the \"character\" everyone expects you to be, and that the real you feels invisible or non-existent behind the script.\n\nI want to tell you that even the most grumpy, stubborn, and uncooperative goblins in the deep dark caves can be coaxed into doing chores if you just offer them a little kindness and a shiny trinket. Maybe your mind is just tired from holding onto too many old memories or worries, and it needs a break from the \"movie screen.\"\n\nTry to imagine your mind not as a cinema, but as a cozy, slightly messy room where you can rearrange the furniture. If you feel like a ghost, perhaps you can try to ground yourself in your physical body right now—feel the weight of your feet on the floor, the texture of your clothes, or the air on your skin. These are the things that remind you you are *here*, not just watching from the sidelines.\n\nIt's okay to take a moment to rest. Even the smallest",
